node.text:
This past trimester in @fit.for.service we have been training to cultivate the full expression of the sacred masculine. Our journey through the Austin summit started with a poetry workshop by the great @inqlife where we learned to alchemize our grievances into gratitude through the medium of spoken word. We entered workshops where we explored the complicated nuances of the psyche, and prepared ourselves to retrain the harsh inner critic into a loving and supportive inner coach. 

To test what we had been learning, we created the Elemental Games. Five teams were charged with representing the five Earth elements with costume and dance, and then offered the opportunity to represent their team in competition. It was one of the most powerful ceremonies any of us have ever been a part of. Before the paint washed off, we came together with a deeper appreciation for every single person who entered the arena. 

We enjoyed a stunning private concert with @satsang, a night of sober celebration, and one of the most potent speeches I have ever heard by the philosopher king Charles Eisenstein. 

I’m so grateful to everyone who participated in Trimester 2. And as my teacher Don Howard always said, there is always another layer. We’ll go together to find that layer this October in Sedona for Trimester 3. If you are interested in applying, click the link in bio or head to aubreymarcus.com/fitforservice

🎥 by @maxwmccoy

node.text:
A psychedelic journey without integration is just a trip to the circus. Who cares what visions you had, or the realms you explored. Did it change your life for the better? This is the litmus test to determine whether a journey was worth it or not. 

My own psychedelic explorations have made me who I am today. They have impacted my work, my romantic life, and my physical health for the better. But they have only done so because I have integrated them into my life. 

I am not recommending anyone take the psychedelic path, that is an absolutely personal choice. But if you feel called, this iss my best advice for integrating your psychedelic journey. 

#psychedelics #psychedelicintegration #cosmicexplorer

node.text:
Contrary to popular opinion, making money doing what you love is absolutely possible. When you’re doing what you love professionally, is it really “work”? 

One of the most effective ways I’ve found to make this a reality is by harnessing the Da Vinci effect; combining 2 or more of your passions to create a niche. When people can see and feel your love for your work, it naturally draws their curiosity out of them to explore what it is you’re offering.
 
#dowhatyoulove #entrepreneurship #abundancemindset

node.text:
This past trimester in @fit.for.service we have been training to cultivate the full expression of the sacred masculine. Our journey through the Austin summit started with a poetry workshop by the great @inqlife where we learned to alchemize our grievances into gratitude through the medium of spoken word. We entered workshops where we explored the complicated nuances of the psyche, and prepared ourselves to retrain the harsh inner critic into a loving and supportive inner coach. 

To test what we had been learning, we created the Elemental Games. Five teams were charged with representing the five Earth elements with costume and dance, and then offered the opportunity to represent their team in competition. It was one of the most powerful ceremonies any of us have ever been a part of. Before the paint washed off, we came together with a deeper appreciation for every single person who entered the arena. 

We enjoyed a stunning private concert with @satsang, a night of sober celebration, and one of the most potent speeches I have ever heard by the philosopher king Charles Eisenstein. 

I’m so grateful to everyone who participated in Trimester 2. And as my teacher Don Howard always said, there is always another layer. We’ll go together to find that layer this October in Sedona for Trimester 3. If you are interested in applying, click the link in bio or head to aubreymarcus.com/fitforservice

🎥 by @maxwmccoy

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Aubrey Marcus in Austin, Texas. May be an image of text that says 'Stories Are Deceiving Our favorite stories are black and white: Us vs. Them... Good vs. Evil... Right vs. Left But the world lives in the grey. Every villain has a hero inside, and every hero has a villainous shadow. If we release our desire for things to be binary, we can start to see the humanity in the opposition. This is the story that creates unity, rather than division.'.

node.text:
We've never lived in a more polarizing time. While it seems that there are a lot of things to fight against, fighting against something is the plot of the story that got us here in the first place. The most powerful movements are fights FOR something more beautiful.

Instead of fighting against censorship, fight FOR free speech.

Instead of fighting against tyranny, fight FOR freedom.

Instead of fighting against any "-ism" fight FOR equality and Love.

Because fighting FOR something allows you to be expressed in the state you are wishing to create. Fighting against something requires you are in a state of conflict, which just creates more conflict.

It may seem to be a subtle shift— it is anything but. The same actions taken in a different energy, are different actions entirely.

#unity #humanity #whatareyoufightingfor

node.text:
A friend told me once that when he met me he felt like he could sense something inauthentic. In some ways he was right... Because I wanted him to like me! It was subtle, sure. But it was there. 

My desire to be liked compelled me to “put a little more English on the cue ball” to use Joe Rogan’s phrase. I was “trying” instead of simply “being”. 

Fear and desire are the two causal forces for any inauthenticity. Perhaps they are actually the same thing at the deepest level. Desire is simply a fear that you do not have everything you need inside of you 🤍

#authenticity #betruetoyourself #youareenough

Remember forgiveness is for you, not for them. It is an act of liberation, for the self. 

How does this save the world? Because you are the world. As Rumi says, "You are not a drop in the ocean, you are the ocean in a drop." And if you can't free yourself from your emotional bondage, the world will never be free.
